  "notes": [
    {
      "title": "Noun of Manner (اسم الهيئة)",
      "titleArabic": "اسم الهيئة",
      "content": [
        "The noun of manner (اسم الهيئة) describes how an action is performed - its manner or state.",
        "For Form I verbs, it follows the pattern فِعْلَة: جِلْسَة (manner of sitting), مِشْيَة (manner of walking)."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Pattern for Form I: فِعْلَة",
        "جَلَسَ → جِلْسَة (manner of sitting)",
        "مَشَى → مِشْيَة (manner of walking)",
        "وَقَفَ → وِقْفَة (manner of standing)"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "جَلَسَ جِلْسَةَ الْعَالِمِ", "english": "He sat in the manner of a scholar" },
        { "arabic": "مَشَتْ مِشْيَةَ الْمُتَكَبِّرِ", "english": "She walked the walk of an arrogant person" },
        { "arabic": "وَقَفَ وِقْفَةَ الْبَطَلِ", "english": "He stood like a hero" },
        { "arabic": "أَكَلَ أِكْلَةَ الْجَائِعِ", "english": "He ate like a hungry person" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Difference Between المرة and الهيئة",
      "titleArabic": "الفرق بين اسم المرة واسم الهيئة",
      "content": [
        "اسم المرة (فَعْلَة) indicates ONE occurrence of the action.",
        "اسم الهيئة (فِعْلَة) describes HOW the action was performed."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "جَلْسَة (فَعْلَة) - one sitting (noun of instance)",
        "جِلْسَة (فِعْلَة) - manner of sitting (noun of manner)",
        "Note the kasra on the first letter for noun of manner",
        "اسم الهيئة is only formed from Form I verbs"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "جَلَسَ جَلْسَةً وَاحِدَةً", "english": "He sat once (instance)" },
        { "arabic": "جَلَسَ جِلْسَةً حَسَنَةً", "english": "He sat in a good manner" },
        { "arabic": "ضَرَبَهُ ضَرْبَةً", "english": "He hit him once (instance)" },
        { "arabic": "ضَرَبَهُ ضِرْبَةً قَوِيَّةً", "english": "He hit him in a strong manner" }
      ]
    }
  ],
